choices.text:
there is no one to learn English with at home. This is why me and my English tutor have more lessons when the whole family is out of the country for one or two weeks,

During the week with my tutor, I get help with my English homework and chat, practice, practice, practice…

Without doubt, I would rate my tutor as 10.01….but first I need to explain why so many firsts!

🌟Recently I had a taster lesson with my tutor and I got very good results and I progressed very quickly.

🌟 I can learn at the evening when the whole family is out of the country.

🌟 I can practice speaking , listening and reading , there’s no barriers, we try everything from grammar , to weather, work , family , friends movie, TV shows.

🌟 I can ask questions, get all the answers and I see how straightforward and easy the lessons with my tutor are.

🌟 As I enjoy learning the language , inspiration flows at twice the usual speed. Ideas come to mind and overflow,never ending .

🌟As a bonus I don’t feel it’s homework, I just get time for myself, just me and my aspects are revived … it’s lovely, I love every minute of this time.

🌟The next minute I hardly notice that I’m knitting my best sweater for one of my friends and finding unending satisfaction.

🌟Home is only 10 minutes away, so
